    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aGuideHub! ‚ù§Ô∏è Bootstrap 5 doesn‚Äôt have any specific css for the hover effect but you can create your own class for the hover effect‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! ‚ù§Ô∏è</p>\n<p>Bootstrap 5 doesn‚Äôt have any specific css for the hover effect but you can create your own class for the hover effect.</p>\n<p>To show the hover effect you can use <code class=\"language-text\">opacity: 0.5</code> css in hover, below is a sample code for the hover effect class.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.hover-effect:hover</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">opacity</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 0.5<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start today‚Äôs tutorial <strong><em>hover class effect using CSS</em></strong></p>\n<p>You can use the above <code class=\"language-text\">hover-effect</code> class on anything like an image, link, text, div, etc.</p>\n<p>Here, I will provide an example of the hover effect on image, text, and div.</p>\n<h2>Mouse over the example using css.</h2>\n<p>To use hover effects I have created the <code class=\"language-text\">.hover-effect</code> class.</p>\n<p>Now, wherever I have to add hover effects I have to just put the <code class=\"language-text\">hover-effect</code> class on those images, div, and text.</p>\n<p>See the below example and the output of it and I also provide a Try it yourself link.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token doctype\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;!</span><span class=\"token doctype-tag\">DOCTYPE</span> <span class=\"token name\">html</span><span 